The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, May 17, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, May 17, 2004				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Prince Anwar Shah Road. One flank dug up for laying large-diameter water pipeline.				 																Talk				 																																	Gilles Deleuze and French Social Thought in the late 20th Century, an exhibition of posters and a round-table discussion presented by Les Amis de la France and Seagull Foundation for the Arts, at 6.30 pm. Participants are Hari Vasudevan, Bhaskar Mukhopadhyaya, Nirmalya Chakravarty and Anjan Ghosh. 				 																																	An illustrated talk on Calcutta heritage sites: an economic valuation by Mousumi Dutta, lecturer, Bethune College, at Victoria Memorial Hall, 6 pm.				 																Fashion				 																																	Confluence 2004, the annual fashion show hosted by NIFT, at ITC Sonar Bangla, 6.30 pm.				 																Workshop				 																																	A dance workshop featuring jazz, salsa, hip hop, funk and ballet for children in the age group of three to 11 at Padatik from 11 am. To be conducted by Ronnie and Gilles Chuyen. A math workshop, too.				 																Art shows				 																																	Summer Show, an all-India exhibition of paintings and sculptures, at CIMA Gallery, from 3 pm to 7 pm.				 																																	20X30, a display of decorative posters presented by Arts amp; Ideas, at Swabhumi, Shop no. 213.				 																																	An exhibition of folk art of Bengal at State Archaeological Museum at Behala, 11 am to 4 pm. 				 																																	Mono prints and paintings by Bidula Basu and Puspita Ray on display at Chemould Art Gallery, from 2 pm to 7 pm.
